cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with semantic segmentation of volumetric data sets such as CT scans. The use of deep neural networks for this task also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The proposed boosted sampling scheme and algorithm for boosting the SGD learning rate schedule suggest that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the mention of state-of-the-art results on a benchmark suggests that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
